snippet: A military appeals court on Wednesday declined to rule on a lawsuit seeking greater access for journalists to court filings and proceedings in the criminal case against Pfc. Bradley Manning.
abstract: Military appeals court declines to rule on lawsuit seeking greater access for journalists to court filings and proceedings in criminal case against Pfc Bradley Manning, who has admitted to leaking confidential government documents to WikiLeaks.
lead_paragraph: A military appeals court on Wednesday declined to rule on a lawsuit seeking greater access for journalists to court filings and proceedings in the criminal case against Pfc. Bradley Manning.

headline.seo: Court Declines to Rule in Wikileaks Complaint
headline.main: Court Declines to Rule in Wikileaks Complaint
headline.print_headline: Court Declines to Rule in WikiLeaks Complaint
